I'm trying to convert a static CloudFormation template to be generated by troposphere. Here is a Policy resource:
```
"contentServiceUserAccessPolicy": {
  "Properties": {
    "PolicyDocument": {
      "Statement": [],
      "Version": "2012-10-17"
    }, 
    "PolicyName": "contentServiceBucketAccess", 
    "Users": [
      {
        "Ref": "contentServiceUser"
      }
    ]
  }, 
  "Type": "AWS::IAM::Policy"
}
```
And the part of the code I'm trying to convert it to is:
```
template.add_resource(iam.Policy(
    "contentServiceUserAccessPolicy",
    PolicyName = "contenServiceBucketAccess",
    Users = [ Ref("contentServiceUser")],
    PolicyDocument = awacs.aws.Policy()
))
```
But I get the following error:
```
AttributeError: Policy object does not support attribute Users
```
According to http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-resource-iam-policy.html, `Users` is an accepted attribute (as well as Roles and Groups), but it doesn't appear in the troposphere source code in https://github.com/cloudtools/troposphere/blob/master/troposphere/iam.py#L42

I'm using version 2.5.1, but have verified the code hasn't changed in master. This is concerning the images function at https://github.com/docker/docker-py/blob/master/docker/api/image.py#L60. The name argument is the value assigned to the 'filter' field, but as far as I can tell from the docker api references, that field was removed in [v1.25](https://docs.docker.com/engine/api/v1.25/#tag/Image) of the docker api. For reference [v1.24](https://docs.docker.com/engine/api/v1.24/#32-images) and [v1.31](https://docs.docker.com/engine/api/v1.31/#tag/Image) the latest.  The equivalent field, as far as I can tell, is the 'reference' field in filters. So this means that the images function will return every image regardless of what you put in the name field if you are using api versions 1.25 and above. The APIClient init comment states that it uses 1.26, but the DEFAULT_DOCKER_API_VERSION is defined to 1.30 -- either way, it will not work as intended unless api version 1.24 is manually specified (tested and it works).

The current code looks like:

```python
        if viz:
            if utils.compare_version('1.7', self._version) >= 0:
                raise Exception('Viz output is not supported in API >= 1.7!')
            return self._result(self._get(self._url("images/viz")))
        params = {
            'filter': name,
            'only_ids': 1 if quiet else 0,
            'all': 1 if all else 0,
        }
```

I made a mod to my local copy to the following right below the if viz block:

```python
        if viz:
            if utils.compare_version('1.7', self._version) >= 0:
                raise Exception('Viz output is not supported in API >= 1.7!')
            return self._result(self._get(self._url("images/viz")))

        if name is not None:
            if filters is None:
                filters = {}
            filters['reference'] = name

        params = { 
            'filter': name,
            'all': 1 if all else 0,
        }
```

After assigning the value of name to the 'reference' option in filters, listing images with name constraints seems to work as expected. Note that I also removed the only_ids field since as far as I can tell it is extraneous since quiet is used later in the function and I didn't see a reference to such a field in any of the api docs. In keeping the 'filter' param, this code still works with pre 1.25 api calls.

