Hi, guys

I'm working on a `python3/tornado/sqlalchemy/graphene + React + Graphql/Relay` solution.

Usually, we use js to run query/mutation on a backend GraphQL schema server.

But use python as client-side is usual. such as: 

```
query Root{
  account{...F0}
}
fragment F0 on AccountApi{
  group(id:"R3JvdXA6Mw=="){
    id
    name
  }
  me{
    lastName
    username
  }
}
```

the group id - `R3JvdXA6Mw==` can be replace by mako template, string format, ...
does graphene plan to supply a more nice query ?

example:

```python
from graphene.client import gq
q = gq(root='''
query Root{
  account
}
''')

f1 = q.fragment("AccountApi", '''
group(id:{group_id}){
    id
    name
  }
  me{
    lastName
    username
  }
''', group_id="R3JvdXA6Mw==")

print(f1.json())
```

Is there a way to automatically resolve a many to many field? 
I.e.:

```
class Payment(models.Model)
    amount = models.IntegerField()
    reasons = models.ManyToManyField('PaymentReason')

class PaymentType(DjangoObjectType):
    class Meta:
        model = Payment
```

Right now I have to extra define reasons like this:
```
class PaymentType(DjangoObjectType):
    reasons = graphene.List(PaymentReasonType)

    def resolve_reasons(self, args, context, info):
        return self.reasons.all()

    class Meta:
        model = Payment
```

Which feels DRY since the relationship is already defined in the Model, why do I need to redfined it in the schema?

The Query i am executing would be (assuming payments returns Payment.objects.all()):
```
{
  payments {
    amount
    reasons {
      reasonValue
    }
  }
}

```

Same would be interesting for Foreign Keys and Reverse Relations.

As originally reported at https://github.com/certbot/certbot/issues/3614#issuecomment-379816901 by @1000i100. It looks like the problem is in the redirect target (`return 301 ...`) which contains a non-ASCII character.

